1:
Yahweh, listen to what I am praying;
\q1 hear me while I cry out to you!
\q1

3:
My life is ending like smoke that disappears;
\q1 I have a big fever which burns my body as a fire burns.
\q1

12:
But Yahweh, you are our king who rules forever;
\q1 people who are not yet born will remember you.
\q1

13:
You will arise and act mercifully toward the people of Jerusalem;
\q2 it is now time for you to do that;
\q1 this is the time for you to be kind to them.
\q1

15:
Yahweh, someday the people of other nations will have an awesome respect for you;
\q1 all the kings on the earth will see that you are very glorious.
\q1

23:
But now you have caused me to become weak while I am still young;
\q2 I think that I will not remain alive very long.
\q1
